<collectionCode id="ED65C7D58D29FFCEFCDCFC9FFCAAAD7C" box="[805,861,775,797]" country="Ukraine" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/c442-9tdv" name="Schmaulhausen Institute of Zoology" pageId="8" pageNumber="303">SIZK</collectionCode>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCB5F108D29FFCEFF22FCA6FBBAAA58" blockId="8.[166,1225,830,1817]" pageId="8" pageNumber="303">
D e s c r i p t i o n. Female (
<typeStatus id="54CFE1B28D29FFCEFE0EFCA6FD94AD38" box="[503,611,830,857]" pageId="8" pageNumber="303">holotype</typeStatus>
). Dorsal shield (
<figureCitation id="134F43958D29FFCEFCE4FCA6FCAEAD38" box="[797,857,830,857]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[174,207,1751,1773]" captionTargetBox="[229,1156,413,1697]" captionTargetId="figure-90@9.[204,1187,382,1715]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 5. Neoseiulus akimovi Kolodochka, sp. n. Female: A — dorsal shield; B — setae J5; C — fragment of ventral body surface; D —chelicera; E — metapodal plates; F1, F2 — spermatheca;G — caudal part of peritremal shield; H — fragment of leg IV; I — genu II (setal abbreviation the same on fig. 1). N. cucumeris (Oudemans, 1930). Female, spermatheca: K — from Karg (1993); L — sample from commercial mite culture." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454851" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454851/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="303">fig. 5</figureCitation>
, A) weakly sclerotized, elongat- ed, with constrictions on level of R1, feebly reticulate in posterior part, with 5 pairs of distinct solenostomes (
<emphasis id="B90083028D29FFCEFEA8FCE6FDBDADF9" box="[337,586,894,920]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="303">gd1, gd2, gd6, gd8, gd9</emphasis>
), 16 pairs of poroids, and 17 pairs of setae acute, smooth (seta Z4 too), thin, short and slightly different in length except Z5 elongated and weekly serrated. Setae J5 short (
<figureCitation id="134F43958D29FFCEFE63FC26FE22ADB8" box="[410,469,958,985]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[174,207,1751,1773]" captionTargetBox="[229,1156,413,1697]" captionTargetId="figure-90@9.[204,1187,382,1715]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 5. Neoseiulus akimovi Kolodochka, sp. n. Female: A — dorsal shield; B — setae J5; C — fragment of ventral body surface; D —chelicera; E — metapodal plates; F1, F2 — spermatheca;G — caudal part of peritremal shield; H — fragment of leg IV; I — genu II (setal abbreviation the same on fig. 1). N. cucumeris (Oudemans, 1930). Female, spermatheca: K — from Karg (1993); L — sample from commercial mite culture." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454851" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454851/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="303">fig. 5</figureCitation>
, B). Length of seta j3 approximately sub-equal to distance to base of seta z2. Setae z2 near half distance between its base to base of z4 which longer than 0.5 distance to seta s4. Seta S5 shoter than other postlateral setae (Z1. S2, S4). Seta Z4 longer than distance between its base and solenostome 
<emphasis id="B90083028D29FFCEFD6AFB86FD4BAA59" box="[659,700,1054,1080]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="303">gd9</emphasis>
and almost reaches base of seta S5.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCB5F108D29FFCEFF22FBA6FC70A8F8" blockId="8.[166,1225,830,1817]" pageId="8" pageNumber="303">
All ventral setae thin, acute, and smooth. Sternal shield with 3 pairs of setae (St1–St3) and 2 pairs of lyrifissures. Setae St4 on separate metasernal platelets each with pore. Ventrianal shield wider than genital shield, elongated, near pentagonal with anterior margin slightly convex, lateral margins slight constricted, circum-anal area of shield with insignificant striation. Narrow transversal sclerotized stria between genital and ventrianal shields. One pair narrow straight-line plates posteroparaxially to setae ZV1. Ventrianal shield with three pairs of short pre-anal setae JV1, JV2, ZV2. Pre-anal solenostomes 
<emphasis id="B90083028D29FFCEFBDBFB66FBBEAB79" box="[1058,1097,1278,1304]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="303">gv3</emphasis>
small and disposed posteroparaxially of setae JV2 (
<figureCitation id="134F43958D29FFCEFD71FA86FD30AB58" box="[648,711,1310,1337]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[167,200,1757,1779]" captionTargetBox="[276,1137,519,1733]" captionTargetId="figure-161@6.[223,1164,495,1749]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 4. Neoseiulus brachychaetus Kolodochka, sp. n. Female: A — dorsal shield; B — fragment of ventral body surface; C — chelicera; D — metapodal plates; E1, E2— spermatheca; F — caudal part of peritremal shield; G — fragment of leg IV; H — genu II (setal abbreviation the same on fig. 1). Male: I — chelicera." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454849" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454849/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="303">fig. 4</figureCitation>
, C). Setae ZV1, ZV3, JV4, JV5, and 4 pairs of small oval platelets on the integument surrounding the ventrianal shield. Chelicerae normal in size. Fixed digit with 3 subapical denticles, movable digit with 1 blunt tooth (
<figureCitation id="134F43958D29FFCEFF57FAE6FF1DABF8" box="[174,234,1406,1433]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[166,199,1486,1508]" captionTargetBox="[255,1143,192,1452]" captionTargetId="figure-90@4.[221,1167,174,1481]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 3. Neoseiulus micmac (Chant et Hansell). Female: A— dorsal shield; B — setae J5; C — fragment of ventral body surface; D 13–14, chelicerae (D — moveable digit; D — fixed digit); E — metapodal plates; F — spermatheca; G — caudal part of peritremal shield; H — fragment of leg IV." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454845" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454845/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="303">fig. 3</figureCitation>
, D). Metapodal plates elongated, anterior platelet smaller than posterior platelet (
<figureCitation id="134F43958D29FFCEFF57FA06FF1CABD8" box="[174,235,1438,1465]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[167,200,1757,1779]" captionTargetBox="[276,1137,519,1733]" captionTargetId="figure-161@6.[223,1164,495,1749]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 4. Neoseiulus brachychaetus Kolodochka, sp. n. Female: A — dorsal shield; B — fragment of ventral body surface; C — chelicera; D — metapodal plates; E1, E2— spermatheca; F — caudal part of peritremal shield; G — fragment of leg IV; H — genu II (setal abbreviation the same on fig. 1). Male: I — chelicera." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454849" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454849/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="303">fig. 4</figureCitation>
, E). Infundibulum of spermatheca relatively large, asymmetrically bell-shaped with wall moderately thickened. Infundibulum gradually narrows from vesicle (sacculus) towards atrium and then suddenly creates progressively convergent part like cervix to clearcut small atrium (
<figureCitation id="134F43958D29FFCEFE8FFA66FE45A878" box="[374,434,1534,1561]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[174,207,1751,1773]" captionTargetBox="[229,1156,413,1697]" captionTargetId="figure-90@9.[204,1187,382,1715]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 5. Neoseiulus akimovi Kolodochka, sp. n. Female: A — dorsal shield; B — setae J5; C — fragment of ventral body surface; D —chelicera; E — metapodal plates; F1, F2 — spermatheca;G — caudal part of peritremal shield; H — fragment of leg IV; I — genu II (setal abbreviation the same on fig. 1). N. cucumeris (Oudemans, 1930). Female, spermatheca: K — from Karg (1993); L — sample from commercial mite culture." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454851" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454851/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="303">fig. 5</figureCitation>
, F 
<figureCitation id="134F43958D29FFCEFE2AFA66FE29A878" box="[467,478,1534,1561]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,199,1755,1777]" captionTargetBox="[266,1143,474,1718]" captionTargetId="figure-14@2.[223,1167,435,1738]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Neoseiulus bicaudus (Wainstein). Female:A — dorsal shield; B — setae J5; C — fragment of ventral body surface; D —chelicera; E — metapodal plates; F — spermatheca; G — caudal part of peritremal shield; H — fragment of leg IV; I, genu II (setal abbreviation: ad — antero-dorsal, pd — post-dorsal; al — antero-lateral, pl — post-lateral; av — antero-ventral)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454837" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454837/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="303">1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="134F43958D29FFCEFE10FA66FE0FA878" box="[489,504,1534,1561]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[174,207,1751,1773]" captionTargetBox="[229,1156,413,1697]" captionTargetId="figure-90@9.[204,1187,382,1715]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 5. Neoseiulus akimovi Kolodochka, sp. n. Female: A — dorsal shield; B — setae J5; C — fragment of ventral body surface; D —chelicera; E — metapodal plates; F1, F2 — spermatheca;G — caudal part of peritremal shield; H — fragment of leg IV; I — genu II (setal abbreviation the same on fig. 1). N. cucumeris (Oudemans, 1930). Female, spermatheca: K — from Karg (1993); L — sample from commercial mite culture." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454851" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454851/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="303">5</figureCitation>
, F 
<figureCitation id="134F43958D29FFCEFDEEFA66FDD1A878" box="[535,550,1534,1561]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,640,662]" captionTargetBox="[348,1091,183,596]" captionTargetId="figure-541@3.[329,1099,174,606]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 2. Neoseiulus bicaudus (Wainstein). Male: A — chelicera; B — ventrianal shield." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454841" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454841/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="303">2</figureCitation>
). Peritremes long, extending beyond bases of setae j3 (
<figureCitation id="134F43958D29FFCEFB5BFA66FF42A858" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[174,207,1751,1773]" captionTargetBox="[229,1156,413,1697]" captionTargetId="figure-90@9.[204,1187,382,1715]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 5. Neoseiulus akimovi Kolodochka, sp. n. Female: A — dorsal shield; B — setae J5; C — fragment of ventral body surface; D —chelicera; E — metapodal plates; F1, F2 — spermatheca;G — caudal part of peritremal shield; H — fragment of leg IV; I — genu II (setal abbreviation the same on fig. 1). N. cucumeris (Oudemans, 1930). Female, spermatheca: K — from Karg (1993); L — sample from commercial mite culture." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454851" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454851/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="303">fig. 5</figureCitation>
, A). Posterior part of peritremal shield widened, curved (
<figureCitation id="134F43958D29FFCEFCB0F986FC73A858" box="[841,900,1566,1593]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[174,207,1751,1773]" captionTargetBox="[229,1156,413,1697]" captionTargetId="figure-90@9.[204,1187,382,1715]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 5. Neoseiulus akimovi Kolodochka, sp. n. Female: A — dorsal shield; B — setae J5; C — fragment of ventral body surface; D —chelicera; E — metapodal plates; F1, F2 — spermatheca;G — caudal part of peritremal shield; H — fragment of leg IV; I — genu II (setal abbreviation the same on fig. 1). N. cucumeris (Oudemans, 1930). Female, spermatheca: K — from Karg (1993); L — sample from commercial mite culture." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454851" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454851/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="303">fig. 5</figureCitation>
, G). Leg IV with three acute macrosetae: on basitarsus — longest, and on tibia and genu markedly shorter (
<figureCitation id="134F43958D29FFCEFBC8F9A6FB9BA838" box="[1073,1132,1598,1625]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[167,200,1757,1779]" captionTargetBox="[276,1137,519,1733]" captionTargetId="figure-161@6.[223,1164,495,1749]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 4. Neoseiulus brachychaetus Kolodochka, sp. n. Female: A — dorsal shield; B — fragment of ventral body surface; C — chelicera; D — metapodal plates; E1, E2— spermatheca; F — caudal part of peritremal shield; G — fragment of leg IV; H — genu II (setal abbreviation the same on fig. 1). Male: I — chelicera." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454849" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454849/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="303">fig. 4</figureCitation>
, H). No macrosetae on other legs. Genu II with 8 setae (2 
<emphasis id="B90083028D29FFCEFD18F9C6FD00A819" box="[737,759,1630,1656]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="303">al</emphasis>
–2 
<emphasis id="B90083028D29FFCEFCE3F9C6FCC0A819" box="[794,823,1630,1656]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="303">ad</emphasis>
, 2 
<emphasis id="B90083028D29FFCEFCA1F9C6FC82A819" box="[856,885,1630,1656]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="303">pd</emphasis>
/ 1 
<emphasis id="B90083028D29FFCEFC67F9C7FC4EA819" box="[926,953,1631,1656]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="303">av</emphasis>
–1 
<emphasis id="B90083028D29FFCEFC24F9C6FC04A819" box="[989,1011,1630,1656]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="303">pl</emphasis>
); setae 
<emphasis id="B90083028D29FFCEFBB0F9C6FB9AA819" box="[1097,1133,1630,1656]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="303">al1</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B90083028D29FFCEFB5CF9C6FB3FA819" box="[1189,1224,1630,1656]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="303">al2</emphasis>
markedly shorter than the rest of the setae on genu II (
<figureCitation id="134F43958D29FFCEFCDDF9E6FC97A8F8" box="[804,864,1662,1689]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[174,207,1751,1773]" captionTargetBox="[229,1156,413,1697]" captionTargetId="figure-90@9.[204,1187,382,1715]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 5. Neoseiulus akimovi Kolodochka, sp. n. Female: A — dorsal shield; B — setae J5; C — fragment of ventral body surface; D —chelicera; E — metapodal plates; F1, F2 — spermatheca;G — caudal part of peritremal shield; H — fragment of leg IV; I — genu II (setal abbreviation the same on fig. 1). N. cucumeris (Oudemans, 1930). Female, spermatheca: K — from Karg (1993); L — sample from commercial mite culture." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454851" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454851/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="303">fig. 5</figureCitation>
, I).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCB5F108D29FFCFFF22F906FE2FAE8E" blockId="8.[166,1225,830,1817]" lastBlockId="9.[174,1232,180,367]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="304" pageId="8" pageNumber="303">
Measurements. Length of dorsal shield from j1 to end of shield, Lds 390; width of dorsal shield, Wds 188; length of ventrianal shield, Lvas 133; max width of ventrianal shield, Wvas 108; distance between pre-anal solenostomes gv3, Lgv3 39; length of tarsus of leg IV, Ltar IV 109. Length of setae: j1 25, j3 34, j4 20, j5 15, j6 20, J2 23, J5 10, 
<geoCoordinate id="EE4039D78D29FFCEFBC2F966FB8EA978" box="[1083,1145,1790,1817]" degrees="4" direction="south" minutes="31" orientation="latitude" pageId="8" pageNumber="303" precision="925" value="-4.5166664">s4 31</geoCoordinate>
, z2 30, z4 34, z5 11, 
<geoCoordinate id="EE4039D78D28FFCFFEBEFF2CFE7EAEAE" box="[327,393,180,207]" degrees="2" direction="south" minutes="37" orientation="latitude" pageId="9" pageNumber="304" precision="925" value="-2.6166668">S2 37</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="EE4039D78D28FFCFFE6FFF2CFE20AEAE" box="[406,471,180,207]" degrees="4" direction="south" minutes="37" orientation="latitude" pageId="9" pageNumber="304" precision="925" value="-4.616667">S4 37</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="EE4039D78D28FFCFFE1DFF2CFDD2AEAE" box="[484,549,180,207]" degrees="5" direction="south" minutes="31" orientation="latitude" pageId="9" pageNumber="304" precision="925" value="-5.5166664">S5 31</geoCoordinate>
, Z1 27, Z4 35, Z5 68, r3 29, R1 29, JV5 43; macrosetae on leg IV: ge 27, ti 30, tar 49.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCB5F108D28FFCFFF1AFF6CFE6AAF6E" blockId="9.[174,1232,180,367]" box="[227,413,244,271]" pageId="9" pageNumber="304">Male unknown.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCB5F108D28FFCCFF1AFE8CFC2AAF6B" blockId="9.[174,1232,180,367]" lastBlockId="10.[166,1225,175,490]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="305" pageId="9" pageNumber="304">
<taxonomicName id="4C7424938D28FFCFFF1AFE8CFE32AF4F" authority="Kolodochka, 2018" authorityName="Kolodochka" authorityYear="2018" box="[227,453,276,302]" class="Arachnida" family="Phytoseiidae" genus="Neoseiulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="9" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="akimovi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B90083028D28FFCFFF1AFE8CFE32AF4F" box="[227,453,276,302]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="304">Neoseiulus akimovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2333E798D28FFCFFE34FE8CFDFBAF4E" box="[461,524,276,303]" pageId="9" pageNumber="304" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
was also misidentified by B. A. Wainstein as “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C7424938D28FFCFFBCBFE8DFB49AF4F" baseAuthorityName="Wainstein" baseAuthorityYear="1962" box="[1074,1214,276,302]" class="Arachnida" family="Phytoseiidae" genus="Neoseiulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="9" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicaudus">
<emphasis id="B90083028D28FFCFFBCBFE8DFB49AF4F" box="[1074,1214,276,302]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="304">N. bicaudus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”. These species resembles each other to some extent but 
<taxonomicName id="4C7424938D28FFCFFCAAFEADFC20AF2F" authority="Kolodochka, 2018" authorityName="Kolodochka" authorityYear="2018" box="[851,983,308,334]" class="Arachnida" family="Phytoseiidae" genus="Neoseiulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="9" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="akimovi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B90083028D28FFCFFCAAFEADFC20AF2F" box="[851,983,308,334]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="304">N. akimovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2333E798D28FFCFFC1BFEACFBD3AF2E" box="[994,1060,308,335]" pageId="9" pageNumber="304" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs by the presence of 5 pair of dorsal solenostomes (gd4 and gd5 absent), setae JV5 smooth and comparatively shorter, 8 setae on genu II, funnel of spermatheca bell-shaped with wall thickened (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7424938D2BFFCCFEB3FF48FE23AE88" baseAuthorityName="Wainstein" baseAuthorityYear="1962" box="[330,468,207,233]" class="Arachnida" family="Phytoseiidae" genus="Neoseiulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="10" pageNumber="305" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicaudus">
<emphasis id="B90083028D2BFFCCFEB3FF48FE23AE88" box="[330,468,207,233]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="305">N. bicaudus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 7 pairs dorsal solenostomes present, setae JV5 long and serrate, 7 setae on genu II, funnel of spermatheca cup-shaped with thin walls).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF0B0F988D28FFCFFF57F94FFBF0A95C" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454851" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6454851" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454851/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="304" startId="9.[174,207,1751,1773]" targetBox="[229,1156,413,1697]" targetPageId="9">
<paragraph id="8BCB5F108D28FFCFFF57F94FFBF0A95C" blockId="9.[174,1233,1751,1853]" pageId="9" pageNumber="304">
Fig. 5. 
<taxonomicName id="4C7424938D28FFCFFF14F94FFDD6A88C" authority="Kolodochka" authorityName="Kolodochka" authorityYear="2018" box="[237,545,1751,1773]" class="Arachnida" family="Phytoseiidae" genus="Neoseiulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="9" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="akimovi" status="sp. n.">
