<subSubSection id="C36E0C9B8D2BFFCCFF22FE97FEDAAC2B" pageId="10" pageNumber="305" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8BCB5F108D2BFFCCFF22FE97FF18AF8B" blockId="10.[166,1225,175,490]" pageId="10" pageNumber="305">
<taxonomicName id="4C7424938D2BFFCCFF22FE97FE4AAF48" authority="Kolodochka, 2018" authorityName="Kolodochka" authorityYear="2018" box="[219,445,271,297]" class="Arachnida" family="Phytoseiidae" genus="Neoseiulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="10" pageNumber="305" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="akimovi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B90083028D2BFFCCFF22FE97FE4AAF48" box="[219,445,271,297]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="305">Neoseiulus akimovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2333E798D2BFFCCFE3CFE97FDF3AF4B" box="[453,516,271,298]" pageId="10" pageNumber="305" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C7424938D2BFFCCFD59FE88FBEBAF4B" authority="(Oudemans, 1930)" baseAuthorityName="Oudemans" baseAuthorityYear="1930" box="[672,1052,271,298]" class="Arachnida" family="Phytoseiidae" genus="Neoseiulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="10" pageNumber="305" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cucumeris">
<emphasis id="B90083028D2BFFCCFD59FE88FCCFAF48" box="[672,824,272,297]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="305">N. cucumeris</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE522E18D2BFFCCFCB1FE97FBE3AF4B" author="Oudemans, A. C." box="[840,1044,271,298]" pageId="10" pageNumber="305" pagination="69 - 74" refId="ref7451" refString="Oudemans, A. C. 1930. Acarologische Aanteekeningen CII. Entomologische Berichte, 8 (172), 69 - 74." type="journal article" year="1930">Oudemans, 1930</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
in general but differs by setae Z4 smooth, by thin-walled of broad infundibulum of spermatheca which narrows from vesicle (sacculus) towards atrium at first gradually but suddenly creates progressively convergent part like cervix to clear-cut small atrium, against Z4 serrate, another form and narrower infundibulum of thick-walled spermatheca, atrium relatively larger and connected to infundibulum by a very short true cervix in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7424938D2BFFCCFC22FE28FB83AFA8" baseAuthorityName="Oudemans" baseAuthorityYear="1930" box="[987,1140,432,457]" class="Arachnida" family="Phytoseiidae" genus="Neoseiulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="10" pageNumber="305" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cucumeris">
<emphasis id="B90083028D2BFFCCFC22FE28FB83AFA8" box="[987,1140,432,457]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="305">N. cucumeris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="134F43958D2BFFCCFB7CFE37FB34AFAB" box="[1157,1219,431,458]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[174,207,1751,1773]" captionTargetBox="[229,1156,413,1697]" captionTargetId="figure-90@9.[204,1187,382,1715]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 5. Neoseiulus akimovi Kolodochka, sp. n. Female: A — dorsal shield; B — setae J5; C — fragment of ventral body surface; D —chelicera; E — metapodal plates; F1, F2 — spermatheca;G — caudal part of peritremal shield; H — fragment of leg IV; I — genu II (setal abbreviation the same on fig. 1). N. cucumeris (Oudemans, 1930). Female, spermatheca: K — from Karg (1993); L — sample from commercial mite culture." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454851" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454851/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="305">fig. 5</figureCitation>
, K, L).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCB5F108D2BFFCCFF22FD97FEDAAC2B" blockId="10.[166,1225,527,586]" pageId="10" pageNumber="305">The new species is named in honour of Prof. Igor A. Akimov, the eminent Ukrainian acarologist.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
